records.addlTxt:
Defendant John A Neumann in court with attorney Adam J. Schleis.  Andrea M Will appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads Guilty to Count 2.  Count 1 is dismissed and read-in.  Victim spoke in court.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (Credit - none), CONSECUTIVE TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE IF REVOKED.
  -  18 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  18 MONTHS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with:  victim unless victim initiates contact
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

RESTITUTION:  $7,410.00 to victim (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DRGOD:  $10.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 90 DAYS - First 45 days with release for work and/or treatment; second 45 days to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  Defendant to report by 6:00 pm on October 28, 2016.  
Transferred allowed to Washington County with NO electronic monitoring.  

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
